content:
When automated prediction writeback fields are configured for a prediction definition that outputs a numerical prediction (regression) or score (binary classification), Einstein Discovery can save predictions directly to Salesforce records for use in reports and list views.

Configure automated prediction writeback in Model Manager. After deployment, Einstein scores newly created or updated records in the Salesforce object and writes the score to the prediction field. Only the prediction is written, not the reasons for the prediction or the suggested ways in which to improve the prediction.

Prediction writeback fields are a special type of custom field that only Einstein can write to. To view predictions, improvements, and related details, users must have the View Einstein Discovery Recommendations permission assigned to their Salesforce account.

To use Automated Prediction Writeback fields:

Select a Salesforce object,
Map all variables in the model to corresponding fields in the Salesforce object or a supplemental dataset.
Assign field-level security to the prediction field (required).
Add this field to existing custom report types and list views just like you do for other custom fields.
The prediction shown in the Einstein Predictions panel on a Lightning record page or Experience Cloud sites page can differ from the prediction shown in the prediction field.

Only the prediction value (or score) is written to the prediction field. If you also want to display the prediction reason and suggested improvements to the predicted outcome, add the Einstein Prediction Lightning component on a Lightning record page.

To map predictions to live Google BigQuery data or Snowflake data, create a live connection.
title: Configuring Automated Prediction Writeback in Salesforce
